# ==============================================================================
# .dockerignore â€” Container Build Context Hygiene
# ==============================================================================
#
# Purpose
# - Reduces Docker build context size and prevents leaking development-only artifacts into the image.
# - Improves build performance and helps keep final images smaller and more reproducible.
#
# What is excluded 
# - Git metadata and repo housekeeping:
#   .git, .gitignore (not needed at runtime; reduces context size)
# - Local Python environment and caches:
#   venv/, __pycache__/, *.pyc (platform-specific, not portable, unnecessary)
# - Local OS junk:
#   .DS_Store, Thumbs.db
# - Docker build recipe files:
#   Dockerfile, .dockerignore (the container does not need its own build instructions at runtime)
# ==============================================================================

# Exclude Git history 
.git
.gitignore

# Exclude local Python environment
venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Exclude local OS junk
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Exclude your Docker files
Dockerfile
.dockerignore